Label: Orion
Description: constellation located on the celestial equator,named for a famed hunter in Greek myth

Label: Ophiuchus
Description: constellation located near the celestial equator,named the Serpentbearer

Label: Pleiades
Description: group of seven stars located in Taurus

Label: Hyades
Description: seven stars in the head of the Bull

Label: Ursa Major
Description: the constellation of the Great Bear, also known as the Wain, Wagon or Plough

Label: Taurus
Description: The Bull, one of the constellations of the Zodiac

Label: Scorpius
Description: The Scorpion, a constellation in located in the southern hemisphere near the center of the Milky Way

Label: Celestial Poles
Description: the two imaginary points in the sky where the Earth's axis of rotation intersects the celestial sphere

Label: Ursa Minor
Description: the contellation of the Little Bear (cf the excellent children's television series)

Label: Draco
Description: the constellation of the Dragon in the far northern sky (cf the character in the excellent children's book series)

Label: Bootes
Description: the constellation of the Plowman in the northern sky

Label: Cepheus
Description: the constellation in the northern sky, named after the King of Aethiopia
